    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix missing eq_f1ap_ue_to_reset function implementation\n\n### Summary\nThe function `eq_f1ap_ue_to_reset()` was referenced in the F1AP codebase but never implemented, causing unexpected behavior when comparing UE contexts for reset operations. This adds the missing implementation and declarations.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/F1AP/f1ap_cu_interface_management.c`: Added implementation of `eq_f1ap_ue_to_reset()`\n- `openair2/F1AP/f1ap_cu_interface_management.h`: Added function declaration\n- `openair2/F1AP/f1ap_du_interface_management.c`: Added implementation of `eq_f1ap_ue_to_reset()`\n- `openair2/F1AP/f1ap_du_interface_management.h`: Added function declaration\n\n### Reproduction\nBefore this fix, calling `eq_f1ap_ue_to_reset()` would result in either:\n1. A linker error if the function was completely missing\n2. Unexpected behavior if a stub or incorrect implementation existed\n\nThe function is needed when processing F1AP RESET messages that target specific UE contexts, where the system needs to compare local UE contexts with those specified in the reset request.\n\nAfter this fix, the function correctly compares UE contexts by checking both the gNB_CU_ue_id and gNB_DU_ue_id fields, returning 1 for matching UEs and 0 otherwise.\n\n"
}